def: Of or pertaining to the country of the ancient Silures; -- aterm applied to the earliest of the Paleozoic eras, and also to thestrata of the era, because most plainly developed in that country.

That which polarizes; especially, the part of a polariscopewhich receives and polarizes the light. It is usually a reflectingplate, or a plate of some crystal, as tourmaline, or a doublyrefracting crystal.
Incapable of erring; infallible; unerring. "Inerabble andrequisite conditions." Sir T. Browne. "Not an inerrable text."Gladstone.
Not interesting of affecting; insignificant; not belonging toone. [Obs.] Addison.
One who pronounces an anathema. Hammond.
Having the petals free, that is, entirely separate from eachother; -- said of both plant and flower.
The state or quality of being melancholy. Hallywell.
